  "texts": [
    "A commonly used quadratic form is:r(x k, u k) = (x k -x ref) ⊤ Q(x k -x ref) + u ⊤ k Ru k,(23)where x ref is the reference state (e.g., nominal frequency or voltage), Q ⪰ 0 is a state weighting matrix, and R ≻ 0 is a control weighting matrix.",
    "This cost function penalizes deviations from the states as well as the control actions so it ensures stable and efficient operation.",
    "A simple form of the cost function has the form of:r(x k, u k) = ω 2 k + αu 2 k,(24)where ω k is the frequency deviation and u k is the control input from the governor or AVR, and α > 0 controls the trade-off between tracking performance and control effort.",
    "By iteratively updating both the value function approximation V (x) and the optimal control u * (t), ADP enables nearoptimal decision-making in real time, even in the presence of system uncertainties and nonlinear dynamics.",
    "In smart grids, this framework allows agents (e.g., DER controllers, loadserving entities) to update control actions in real-time based on observed system evolution."
